00:05:33.270 --> 00:05:37.280
Throughout his career, the
honorable Norman Y. Mineta served

00:05:37.280 --> 00:05:41.100
as US Secretary of Transportation,
US Secretary of Commerce,

00:05:41.100 --> 00:05:43.100
and as a member of Congress.

00:05:43.100 --> 00:05:47.640
In 1942 when he was ten
years old, Secretary Mineta

00:05:47.640 --> 00:05:51.140
and his family were among
the 120,000 Americans

00:05:51.140 --> 00:05:54.540
of Japanese ancestry
forced from their homes

00:05:54.540 --> 00:05:58.630
and into internment camps by the
US government following the attack

00:05:58.630 --> 00:06:00.790
on Pearl Harbor by Japan.

00:06:00.790 --> 00:06:05.580
They would remain interned for
the duration of World War II.

00:06:05.580 --> 00:06:08.230
Secretary Mineta and
his family are interned

00:06:08.230 --> 00:06:11.430
in a camp near Cody, Wyoming.

00:06:11.430 --> 00:06:15.690
It was there that Mineta, a
Boy Scout, met Al Simpson,

00:06:15.690 --> 00:06:19.280
who visited the camp with
his local Boy Scout troop.

00:06:19.280 --> 00:06:23.090
This marked the beginning
of a life-long friendship.

00:06:23.090 --> 00:06:28.150
Returning to his hometown of
San Jose, California in 1945,

00:06:28.150 --> 00:06:32.280
he graduated from the University of
California at Berkeley and served

00:06:32.280 --> 00:06:36.880
as a US Army intelligence officer
during the Korean conflict.

00:06:36.880 --> 00:06:41.480
In 1967 he became the first
Asian Pacific-American member

00:06:41.480 --> 00:06:43.870
of the San Jose City Council,

00:06:43.870 --> 00:06:47.460
becoming the city's
vice-mayor in 1968.

00:06:47.460 --> 00:06:51.830
In 1974 he was elected
to the US Congress

00:06:51.830 --> 00:06:54.340
where he served for 20 years.

00:06:54.340 --> 00:06:57.260
Throughout that time, Mineta
was a constant advocate

00:06:57.260 --> 00:06:59.800
in the area of civil rights.

00:06:59.800 --> 00:07:02.860
He founded and served
as the first chairman

00:07:02.860 --> 00:07:06.390
of the Congressional Asian
Pacific-American Caucus.

00:07:06.390 --> 00:07:08.420 position:56%
He served as the principal authorize

00:07:08.420 --> 00:07:13.830 position:56%
and driving force behind what became
the Civil Liberties Act of 1988,

00:07:13.830 --> 00:07:16.170
which officially apologized
to Americans

00:07:16.170 --> 00:07:19.580
of Japanese ancestry
for the internment.

00:07:19.580 --> 00:07:24.030
In 2000, President Bill Clinton
appointed Mineta Secretary

00:07:24.030 --> 00:07:28.220
of Commerce, making him the
first Asian Pacific-American

00:07:28.220 --> 00:07:30.120
cabinet secretary.

00:07:30.120 --> 00:07:34.980
In 2001, President George W.
Bush appointed Mineta Secretary

00:07:34.980 --> 00:07:39.320
of Transportation where
he served until 2006 --

00:07:39.320 --> 00:07:42.650
one of the very few Americans
to have served in the cabinet

00:07:42.650 --> 00:07:44.750
of presidents from two parties.

00:07:44.750 --> 00:07:49.530
Following the terrorist
attacks of September 11th, 2001,

00:07:49.530 --> 00:07:51.280
Mineta guided the creation

00:07:51.280 --> 00:07:55.560
of the Transportation Security
Administration, an agency with more

00:07:55.560 --> 00:08:00.310
than 65,000 employees, marking
the largest mobilization

00:08:00.310 --> 00:08:04.600
of a new federal agency
since World War II.

00:08:05.650 --> 00:08:09.050
Alan K. Simpson served in
the United States Senate

00:08:09.050 --> 00:08:11.150 position:56%
as a member of the Republican Party.

00:08:11.150 --> 00:08:14.210
In addition to his public
service, Simpson taught

00:08:14.210 --> 00:08:17.260
at the Joan Shorenstein
Center on the Press, Politics

00:08:17.260 --> 00:08:21.600
and Public Policy at Harvard's
University Kennedy's School

00:08:21.600 --> 00:08:25.180
of Government and served for
two years as the director

00:08:25.180 --> 00:08:28.660
of the Institute of Politics
at the Kennedy School.

00:08:28.660 --> 00:08:34.340
Simpson graduated from the
University of Wyoming in 1954.

00:08:34.340 --> 00:08:39.180
Upon graduation, he was
commissioned as an ROTC officer.

00:08:39.180 --> 00:08:42.670
He served overseas in the
fifth infantry division

00:08:42.670 --> 00:08:46.980
and in the second armor division
in the final months of the army

00:08:46.980 --> 00:08:49.160
of occupation in Germany.

00:08:49.160 --> 00:08:54.490 position:56%
Following his honorable discharge in
1956, he returned to the University

00:08:54.490 --> 00:08:57.290
of Wyoming to complete
his study of law,

00:08:57.290 --> 00:09:01.650
earning his juris doctorate
degree in 1958.

00:09:01.650 --> 00:09:06.780
After serving for a short time as
Wyoming Assistant Attorney General,

00:09:06.780 --> 00:09:10.250
Simpson joined his father in
the law firm of Simpson, Kepler,

00:09:10.250 --> 00:09:13.590 position:56%
and Simpson in his hometown of Cody.

00:09:13.590 --> 00:09:16.730
He would practice law there
for the next 18 years.

00:09:16.730 --> 00:09:19.380 position:56%
During that time, he was very active

00:09:19.380 --> 00:09:22.500
in all civic community
and state activities.

00:09:22.500 --> 00:09:26.870
He also served ten
years as City Attorney.

00:09:26.870 --> 00:09:31.750
He was elected to the United
States Senate in November 1978

00:09:31.750 --> 00:09:35.170
and served until early 1997.

00:09:35.170 --> 00:09:41.040
From 1985 to 1995, Simpson
was the Republican Whip,

00:09:41.040 --> 00:09:44.250
the assistant Republican
leader in the Senate.

00:09:44.250 --> 00:09:47.350
During his time in office
he was chairman the Veterans

00:09:47.350 --> 00:09:48.880
Affairs Committee.

00:09:48.880 --> 00:09:51.720
He also chaired the Immigration
and Refugee Subcommittee

00:09:51.720 --> 00:09:56.090
of the Judiciary, the Nuclear
Regulation Subcommittee,

00:09:56.090 --> 00:10:00.770
the Social Security Subcommittee,
and the Committee on Aging.

00:10:00.770 --> 00:10:06.380
In early 2010 he was named to
cochair the National Commission

00:10:06.380 --> 00:10:09.540 position:56%
on Fiscal Responsibility and Reform,

00:10:09.540 --> 00:10:13.030
focused on tackling the
United States' deficit.

00:10:13.030 --> 00:10:14.970
He was a member of
the Iraq Study Group

00:10:14.970 --> 00:10:18.850
and the Commission on
Presidential Debates.

00:10:18.850 --> 00:10:22.470
The conversation will be
