00:46:45.200 --> 00:46:50.670
Why, Senator Simpson, were you able
to get immigration legislation --

00:46:50.670 --> 00:46:53.870
landmark legislation -- in 1986?

00:46:53.870 --> 00:46:57.950
And is it ever going to be possible

00:46:57.950 --> 00:47:01.330
in the early part of
the 21st century?

00:47:01.330 --> 00:47:02.630
&gt;&gt; Alan Simpson: Well,

00:47:02.630 --> 00:47:06.990
when we started Ron Mazzoli
was a Democrat from Kentucky.

00:47:06.990 --> 00:47:09.890
Norm knew him well.

00:47:09.890 --> 00:47:14.740 position:56%
And he was the chairman of judiciary
and the Subcommittee on Immigration.

00:47:14.740 --> 00:47:18.810
And I said, "Why are we having
a hearing in the House?"

00:47:18.810 --> 00:47:24.600
on the issue of whatever it was,
security or whatever, or amnesty --

00:47:24.600 --> 00:47:26.740
which we changed the
word to legalization,

00:47:26.740 --> 00:47:30.420
which threw all of them off.

00:47:30.420 --> 00:47:33.030
And you have to learn how
to throw them off, you know,

00:47:33.030 --> 00:47:37.510 position:56%
